  467|       |   *
  468|       |   * To put some numbers on it, imagine we start with a = 34 and c = 27:
  469|       |   *
  470|       |   *  ROUND_10(34) + 27 = 40 + 27 = 67
  471|       |   *
  472|       |   * but also, we can split 27 up into 20 and 7 and do this:
  473|       |   *
  474|       |   *  ROUND_10(34 + 20) + 7 = ROUND_10(54) + 7 = 60 + 7 = 67
  475|       |   *                ^^    ^
